properties.sfomuseum:description: Flight information packet issued by Air France for Boeing and Caravelle aircraft fleet.a. blue folder titled “Le plus grand reseau du monde” with montage of full color illustrations depicting various international landmarks representing Rio de Janeiro, Japan, Egypt, Greece, and London; tri-fold format with two pockets containing inserts b-i;b, c. circular luggage label depicting two jets in flight; blue and white with red “Air France” logotype;d. airport information titled “Paris Orly”; blue and white pamphlet containing airport information printed in French and English; tri-fold format;e. traveler information titled “Reconfirmation obligatoire”; blue and red text printed in French and English containing passenger confirmation instructions; double-sided sheet;f. comment card titled “Monsieur le Directeur General”; light blue and white cover depicting stylized globe; suggestion card printed in French, English, and Spanish; tri-fold format;g. pamphlet with inflight information titled “Bon voyage jet / Air France”; light blue cover with colorful block text; contains illustrated information printed in French and English; multipage booklet;h. wine bar menu; gray background with color illustration of champagne bottle and glassware branded with flag symbols; tri-fold format;i. route map; yellow and blue globe design over black and white image of clouds; folded multipage booklet.
properties.sfomuseum:dimensions: 10 x 6 x 1/4 inches (25.4 x 15.2 x .6 cm)
